cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.EM

The paper discusses the design of Deep Neural Nets for speech recognition and computer vision, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of design principles for embedded microprocessor architectures, which falls under the sub-category of cs.EM (Embedded Systems). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a playbook for creating small Deep Neural Nets, which is related to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
